## Why This Is Asked
Drift detection ensures model reliability and safe fallbacks in production scoring.

## Key Concepts
- Drift detection across model_version switches
- Telemetry fields: drift_flag, drift_reason, score_change_pct, last_model_version, last_score
- Fallback routing and drift alerts
- Observability and basic tests for drift, isolation, and rollback

## Code Example
```javascript
function checkDrift(currentScore, lastScore, lastModelVersion, currentModelVersion, threshold=0.15){
  const drift = Math.abs(currentScore - lastScore);
  const versionChanged = currentModelVersion !== lastModelVersion;
  const driftFlag = drift > threshold || versionChanged;
  const driftReason = versionChanged ? 'model_version_change' : (drift > threshold ? 'score_change' : 'none');
  const scoreChangePct = lastScore ? ((currentScore - lastScore) / Math.abs(lastScore)) * 100 : 0;
  return { driftFlag, driftReason, scoreChangePct };
}
```

